article.description: Kris Martin had 19 points off the bench to lead Colorado State to a 78-65 win over Air Force on Saturday.
article.headline: Martin scores 19 to lift Colorado St. over Air Force 78-65
article.linkText: Martin scores 19 to lift Colorado St. over Air Force 78-65
article.story: AIR FORCE ACADEMY, Colo. -- Kris Martin had 19 points off the bench to lead Colorado State to a 78-65 win over Air Force on Saturday. Nico Carvacho scored 10 points with 13 rebounds for his second double-double of the week. David Roddy had 13 points for Colorado State (13-7, 4-3 Mountain West Conference), which won its fourth straight game and sixth in its last seven. Kendle Moore added 13 points. Isaiah Stevens had 11 points. Lavelle Scottie had 16 points for the Falcons (9-10, 3-4) as did Sid Tomes. A.J. Walker had 11 points. Colorado State matches up against Fresno State at home on Wednesday. Air Force plays Utah State on the road on Tuesday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
